class.name: CellResources
class.description:
This MO models all basic physical and transport channels related to a Node B Local Cell. Basic physical channels: PCPICH, SCPICH, PSCH, SSCH and PCCPCH. Transport channels: BCH.
The RDN of this MO is CellResources=1.
Persistent: No

attribute.name: cellResourcesId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: Defines the operational state.

attribute.name: numOfBch
attribute.description: Current number of BCHs (Broadcast CHannels) in the cell. The BCH is a fixed rate point to multi point downlink channel, used to convey system information in the whole coverage area of the cell.

attribute.name: numOfPccpch
attribute.description: Current number of PCCPCHs (Primary Common Control Physical CHannel) in the cell. This downlink physical channel carries the transport channel BCH.

attribute.name: numOfPcpich
attribute.description: Current number of PCPICHs (Primary Common Pilot CHannel) in the cell. This is a fixed rate downlink physical channel that carries a predefined symbol sequence. PCPICH is used as phase reference for other downlink physical channels. No transport channel is carried on PCPICH.

attribute.name: numOfPsch
attribute.description: Current number of PSCHs (Primary Synchronization CHannel) in the cell. This is a downlink physical channel used to find the scrambling code of the cell. The PSCH transmits the Primary Synchronization Code, which is the same for every cell in the system and known by each UE. It is sent simultaneously with the transmission on the SSCH. No transport channel is carried on PSCH.

attribute.name: numOfScpich
attribute.description: Current number of SCPICHs (Secondary Common Pilot CHannel) in the cell. This is a fixed rate downlink physical channel that carries a predefined symbol sequence. SCPICH is used as phase reference for other downlink physical channels on a second antenna branch in certain MIMO configurations. No transport channel is carried on SCPICH.

attribute.name: numOfSsch
attribute.description: Current number of SSCHs (Secondary Synchronization CHannel) in the cell. This is a downlink physical channel used to find the scrambling code of the cell. SSCH transmits a sequence of 15 codes, simultaneously with transmission on the PSCH. By identifying the sequence the UE can derive the primary scrambling code of the cell. No transport channel is carried on SSCH.

attribute.name: maxNumEulUsers
attribute.description:
Maximum number of serving EUL users allowed per cell.
Alarm Licensed Capacity Exceeded is given if:
• administrativeState=UNLOCKED and • maxNumEulUsers higher than the upper limit and • Emergency Unlock is not activated Where upper limit is: • License key value if Licensed capacity 'Number of EUL users' is enabled (see licenseState in MO CapacityState) or • default value (maximum 4 EUL users) if license key is disabled.
During Emergency Unlock, maximum 128 EUL users are allowed in each cell.
attribute.takesEffect: Increase takes effect immediately. Decrease takes gradual effect; existing users are allowed to terminate normally until the new limit is reached. No new users are allowed until below limit.

attribute.name: maxNumHsdpaUsers
attribute.description:
Maximum number of HSDPA users allowed per cell.
Alarm Licensed Capacity Exceeded is given if:
• administrativeState=UNLOCKED and • maxNumHsdpaUsers higher than the upper limit and • Emergency Unlock is not activated Where upper limit is: • License key value if Licensed capacity 'Number of HSDPA Users per cell' is enabled (see licenseState in MO CapacityState) or • default value (maximum 16 HSDPA users) if license key is disabled.
During Emergency Unlock, maximum 128 HSDPA users are allowed in each cell.
attribute.takesEffect: Increase takes effect immediately. Decrease takes gradual effect; existing users are allowed to terminate normally until the new limit is reached. No new users are allowed until below limit.

attribute.name: maxNumHsPdschCodes
attribute.description:
Maximum number of HS-PDSCH codes allowed per cell.
Alarm Licensed Capacity Exceeded is given if:
• administrativeState=UNLOCKED and • maxNumHsPdschCodes higher than the upper limit and • Emergency Unlock is not activated Where upper limit is: • License key value if Licensed capacity 'Number of HSDPA Codes per cell' is enabled (see licenseState in MO CapacityState) or • default value (maximum 5 HS-PDSCH codes) if license key is disabled.
During Emergency Unlock, maximum 15 HS-PDSCH codes are allowed in each cell.
attribute.takesEffect: Increase takes effect immediately. Decrease takes effect gracefully (if more codes than the new limit are setup by RNC, the new limit will not apply until the RNC has reconfigured the physical shared channel so that less codes than the new limit are used).

attribute.name: eulMcActivationDelayTime
attribute.description:
Activation delay time for secondary UL carrier in serving Node B.
This delay ensures that RNC and UE have time to measure secondary carrier before secondary UL carrier activation in serving Node B. This will mitigate interference to neighboring cells from secondary carrier in heterogeneous network case. Delay applies to all EUL Multi-Carrier users with their primary serving E-DCH cell in this cell.
Set to 20 (1000 ms) for cells that act as primary E-DCH cell, when neighboring cell on corresponding secondary carrier exists, and no corresponding neighboring cell on primary carrier is available. Otherwise, set to 0.

class.name: NodeBSectorCarrier
class.description: This MO models a carrier frequency that is broadcast in a sector.

attribute.name: nodeBSectorCarrierId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: Defines the operational state.

attribute.name: bandwidthDl
attribute.description:
DL carrier bandwidth.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: bandwidthUl
attribute.description:
UL carrier bandwidth.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: cellRange
attribute.description:
Maximum range for random access detection.
For soft handover, RBS adds soft handover margin internally. Note: actual cell range resolution is 3 chips, that is, about 234 m.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.dependencies:
If between default value and 80 km, either optional feature is required: "Extended Cell Range 80 km" or "Extended Cell Range 200 km". If more than 80 km, "Extended Cell Range 200 km" is required.
For a sector carrier that is part of a local cell using more than one sector carrier, the default value must not be exceeded, even if any of the licenses exists.
attribute.takesEffect: Next cell setup.

attribute.name: numOfRxAntennas
attribute.description:
Number of UL antennas.
Features Psi-Coverage and Combined Cell require same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: numOfTxAntennas
attribute.description:
Number of DL antennas.
Features Psi-Coverage and Combined Cell require same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: partOfSectorPower
attribute.description:
Part of total sector power allocated for sector carrier.
Output power is evenly distributed over antenna connectors, used for TX transmission allocated for the sector carrier. If total power for each antenna connector is over 100% at cell unlock, an alarm is generated. Local cell must be locked to prevent transmission.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute for all NodeBSectorCarriers in a given NodeBLocalCell. Total cell power must be equally distributed over all NodeBSectorCarriers, and their sum not over 100%.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: sectorEquipmentFunctionRef
attribute.description: Reference to a SectorEquipmentFunction MO.

attribute.name: eulMaxOwnUuLoad
attribute.description:
Maximum allowed contribution to UL interference rise from own cell carrier traffic.
Scheduler limits E-DCH power based on this parameter.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.

attribute.name: eulMaxRotCoverage
attribute.description:
Maximum Rise over Thermal level allowed to preserve coverage.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.

attribute.name: eulThermalLevelPrior
attribute.description: The anticipated uplink noise floor of the unloaded RBS, including feeder and TMA contributions.
attribute.takesEffect: At next setup of cell. If cell is setup and the noise floor is locked, at commit. If cell is setup and the noise floor is unlocked, at next noise floor lock.

attribute.name: eulNoiseFloorLock
attribute.description:
Locks the noise floor level for RoT calculation to the given value, when set. The locked level is shown by the attribute eulLockedNoiseFloor.
Attribute is empty -> The noise floor level is not locked. Value = -1 -> The noise floor level is locked to current level.
If the cell is setup, the value -1 locks the noise floor to the current estimated noise floor level. If the cell is not setup, the value -1 locks the noise floor to the value given by eulThermalLevelPrior at next cell setup.
The level used for the locked noise floor will be lost at next cell deletion.

attribute.name: maxDlPowerCapability
attribute.description: Maximum DL power capability for sector carrier.
attribute.specification: 3GPP TS 25.433, NBAP, UTRAN Iub interface NBAP signalling

attribute.name: minDlPowerCapability
attribute.description: Minimum DL power capability for sector carrier.
attribute.specification: 3GPP TS 25.433, NBAP, UTRAN Iub interface NBAP signalling

attribute.name: eulLockedNoiseFloor
attribute.description: The noise floor level used when the noise floor is locked by eulNoiseFloorLock.

attribute.name: rfBranchRxRef
attribute.description: A list of references to MOs RfBranch and CcBranch instances, LDNs. These MOs represent the RF branches the NodeBSectorCarrier shall use for RX. If no reference is specified carrier allocation is based on the RF Branch MOM list (default behavior).
attribute.dependencies: Referenced RfBranch(es) or CcBranch(es) must belong to the same MO SectorEquipmentFunction that is referenced from this NodeBSectorCarrier.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: rfBranchTxRef
attribute.description: A list of references to MO RfBranch instances, LDNs. These MOs represents the RF branches the NodeBSectorCarrier shall use for TX. If no reference is specified carrier allocation is based on the RF Branch MOM list (default behavior).
attribute.dependencies: Referenced RfBranch(es) must belong to the same MO SectorEquipmentFunction that is referenced from this NodeBSectorCarrier.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: fccRotMarginHigh
attribute.description:
Rise over Thermal margin relative eulMaxRotCoverage.
Defines high Rise over Thermal threshold for UL Fast Congestion Control. Stabilizes cell carrier Rise over Threshold by control of EUL serving cell traffic.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.dependencies: Ignored unless serviceState = OPERABLE for feature UlFcc.

attribute.name: fccRotMarginLow
attribute.description:
Rise over Thermal margin relative eulMaxRotCoverage.
Defines low Rise over Thermal threshold for UL Fast Congestion Control. Stabilizes cell carrier Rise over Thermal by control of EUL serving cell traffic.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell.
attribute.dependencies: Ignored unless serviceState = OPERABLE for feature UlFcc.

attribute.name: latitude
attribute.description:
The latitude of the corresponding sector antenna, according to a certain geodetic datum (see attribute geoDatum). Allows a maximum resolution of 2.4 m. The integer value is calculated as follows based on a position expressed in degrees (dd), minutes (mm) and seconds (ss.s), where dd has a value between 0 and 90:
latitude = ((dd + mm/60 + ss.s/3600) / 90) x 8388608
Example: Paris Orly airport has latitude 4542009 according to WGS84.

attribute.name: longitude
attribute.description:
The longitude of the corresponding sector antenna, according to a certain geodetic datum (see attribute geoDatum). Allows a maximum resolution of 2.4 m. The integer value is calculated as follows based on a position expressed in degrees (ddd), minutes (mm) and seconds (ss.s), where ddd has a value between -180 and 180:
longitude = ((ddd + mm/60 + ss.s/3600) / 360) x 16777216
Example: Paris Orly airport has longitude 110422 according to WGS84.

attribute.name: latHemisphere
attribute.description:
Defines the latitudinal hemisphere.
Example:
Paris has latHemisphere = NORTH
Cape Town has latHemisphere = SOUTH

attribute.name: beamDirection
attribute.description:
Beam direction of the corresponding sector antenna.
Use value "000" to "359", to define angel for beam direction.
Examples: • 000 = North • 090 = East • 180 = South • 270 = West
Unit: 1°

attribute.name: geoDatum
attribute.description:
Denotes the geodetic (geographic) datum for this sector.
Example: WGS84 (World Geodetic System 1984).

attribute.name: height
attribute.description:
Height above ground.
Example: 1015 = 10.15 meters
Unit: 1 cm

attribute.name: configuredMaxTxPower
attribute.description:
Maximum absolute output power of sector carrier.
Output power is evenly distributed over antenna connectors used for TX transmission by the sector carrier, unless attribute txBranchAPower is set.
Feature Psi-Coverage requires same attribute value for all NodeBSectorCarriers in given NodeBLocalCell. Total cell power must be equally distributed over all sector carriers.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: numOfBranchWithNbir
attribute.description: The number of branches where Narrowband Interference Rejection is currently active.

attribute.name: nbirAlgorithm
attribute.description: Selects which Narrowband Interference Rejection algorithm to use on cell carrier of Radio Units when feature NBIR is activated.
attribute.dependencies: Ignored unless serviceState = OPERABLE for feature Narrowband Interference Rejection.
attribute.takesEffect: At next activation of feature 'Narrowband Interference Rejection'.

attribute.name: nbirFixedNotchPosition
attribute.description: Defines notch position for each cell carrier when feature Narrowband Interference Rejection is activated and nbirAlgorithm is FIXED_NOTCH_NBIR.
attribute.dependencies: Ignored unless serviceState = OPERABLE for feature Narrowband Interference Rejection.
attribute.takesEffect: At next activation of feature 'Narrowband Interference Rejection'.

attribute.name: dlPowerOffsetCombinedCell
attribute.description: Power offset of PCPICH for this NodeBSectorCarrier.
attribute.dependencies: Ignored unless a Combined Cell configuration, i.e. several NodeBSectorCarriers in the NodeBLocalCell connected to different SectorEquipmentFunctions.
attribute.takesEffect: At next cell setup
attribute.precondition: Usage state of parent NodeBLocalCell must be idle (cell must not be setup), before setting this attribute.

attribute.name: txPowerPersistentLock
attribute.description: Indicates if attributes configuredMaxTxPower and txBranchAPower are locked or not. When true, attributes configuredMaxTxPower and txBranchAPower cannot be changed and MO NodeBSectorCarrier cannot be deleted. Note: This attribute is only intended to be used on mRBS and mRRU.
attribute.precondition: Once set to true there is no possibility to change the value back to false unless a node re-integration is performed.

attribute.name: txBranchAPower
attribute.description:
Maximum absolute output power of carrier branch A.
When numOfTxAntennas=1, txBranchAPower is ignored When numOfTxAntennas=2 then • if txBranchAPower is not set (empty), output power is evenly distributed between TX branches of a sector carrier. • if txBranchAPower has a value, maximum absolute output power of carrier branch B is equal to configuredMaxTxPower - txBranchAPower.
attribute.dependencies: txBranchAPower must be less than configuredMaxTxPower. Power relation between carrier branch A and carrier branch B is not allowed to differ more than 40 dB i.e. 0.0001<(txBranchAPower/(configuredMaxTxPower-txBranchAPower))<10000.
attribute.takesEffect: At next unlock of Node B Local Cell.

attribute.name: noiseFloorEstimationMode
attribute.description: The noise floor estimation algorithm selection parameter.

class.name: CommonChannelResourcesDl
class.description:
This MO models all physical and transport channels related to the downlink common channels. Physical channels: SCCPCH, PICH and AICH. Transport channel: FACH and PCH.
The RDN of this MO is CommonChannelResourcesDl=1.
Persistent: No

attribute.name: commonChannelResourcesDlId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: Defines the operational state.

attribute.name: numOfAich
attribute.description: Current number of AICHs (Acquisition Indication CHannel) in the cell. AICH is a fixed rate downlink physical channel that carries the acquisition indications for reception of preambles on RACH. No transport channel is carried on AICH.

attribute.name: numOfFach
attribute.description: Current number of FACHs (Forward Access link CHannel) in the cell. FACH is a downlink common transport channel is used by the network to send messages to a specific UE when no dedicated channels have been established.

attribute.name: numOfPch
attribute.description: Current number of PCHs (Paging CHannel) in the cell. PCH is a downlink common control channel used by the network to broadcast paging messages to find a UE when no dedicated channels have been established.

attribute.name: numOfPich
attribute.description: Current number of PICHs (Paging Indication CHannel) in the cell. PICH is a downlink physical channel used to notify UEs that they must listen for paging messages on the PCH. No transport channel is carried on PICH.

attribute.name: numOfSccpch
attribute.description: Current number of SCCPCHs (Secondary Common Control Physical CHannel) in the cell. SCCPCH is a downlink physical channel that carries the transport channels FACH or PCH.

class.name: CommonChannelResourcesUl
class.description:
This MO models all physical and transport channels related to the uplink common channels. Physical channels: PRACH. Transport channel: RACH.
The RDN of this MO is CommonChannelResourcesUl=1.
Persistent: No

attribute.name: commonChannelResourcesUlId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description: The availability status. It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: Defines the operational state.

attribute.name: numOfPrach
attribute.description: Current number of PRACHs (Physical Random Access CHannel) in the cell. PRACH is an uplink physical channel used to carry RACH.

attribute.name: numOfRach
attribute.description: Current number of RACHs (Random Access CHannel) in the cell. RACH is an uplink common control channel used by any UE to send messages to the network when no dedicated channels have been established.

class.name: EDchResourcesCell
class.description:
This MO models the Enhanced Uplink Shared Channel resources related to a Node B Local Cell. They are set up through Iub.
The RDN of this MO is EDchResourcesCell=1.
Persistent: No

attribute.name: eDchResourcesCellId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

class.name: DlPowerSharing
class.description:
This MO models the HSDPA Mixed Mode Dynamic Power Sharing of a PA.
The RDN of this MO is DlPowerSharing=n.
Persistent: Yes

attribute.name: dlPowerSharingId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: extraPowerHsdpaMixedMode
attribute.description: Maximum borrowed power from other standards on the PA referenced by rfBranchTxRef.
attribute.dependencies: Ignored if no MO NodeBLocalCell is referenced by nodeBLocalCellRef.

attribute.name: rfBranchTxRef
attribute.description: Refers to RF branch instance corresponding to shared PA.

attribute.name: nodeBLocalCellRef
attribute.description: List of NodeBLocalCell MOs using rfBranchTxRef as TX branch and with NodeBLocalCell::featCtrlHsdpaMmPowerSharing = ON.
